                <div class="t4a_post_content">
                	<div class="t4a_post_comments t4a_link_noborder">
                    	                    	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/news/applepi-baker-v1-5-update/#comments" title="<i class='icon-comments-alt'></i> Comments - Give us your opinion, and read opinions of others ... - So far we have 3 comments."><i class="icon-comments-alt"></i> 3</a>
                    </div>
                	<p>ApplePi-Baker, the application I developed for Mac OS X user that like to work with the Raspberry Pi, is now available in version 1.5.<br />
With ApplePi-Baker, you can write an IMG file to an SD-Card, prepare an SD-Card for NOOBS use, and make a backup of an SD-Card.</p>
<p>This new release allows ZIP compression of the IMG file after creating a backup.</p>
<p>This release will now also recognize USB sticks or SD-Cards that are not formatted in a format recognized by your Mac &#8211; for example ext3 or ext4, and will be able to make a backup of that as well.</p>
<p>See the <a title="MacOS X – ApplePi Baker – Prep SD-Cards for IMG or NOOBS" href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/hardware/raspberry-pi/macosx-apple-pi-baker/">ApplePi-Baker article</a> or the <a title="Downloadable Files" href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/downloads/">Downloads Page</a> for download and details. Enjoy <img class="t4a_smiley" src="/wp-content/themes/tweaking4all/css/images/emoticons/t4a_cool.png" alt="" width="32" height="32" /> &#8230;</p>
