                    <h2><a href='http://www.tweaking4all.com/news/applepi-baker-v1-4-update/'>ApplePi-Baker v1.4 update</a></h2>
                </div> 
                
                <div class="t4a_post_image t4a_link_noborder">
                	<img src="http://www.tweaking4all.com/wp-content/themes/tweaking4all/css/images/featured_image_news.png" alt="ApplePi-Baker v1.4 update" width="180" height="151"/><ul><li style="color:#444"><i class="icon-user"></i><ul><li title="Level of Difficulty - <strong>Not applicable</strong> - Super easy or just information."><i class="icon-star-empty"></i><i class="icon-star-empty"></i><i class="icon-star-empty"></i></li></ul></li></ul>                    
                    
                    
					                    <ul><li><i class="icon-folder-close-alt">
                    	</i> 
                            <ul>
                            	<li><a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/category/news/" title="<i class='icon-folder-close-alt'> News &amp; Updates - View all articles in this Category">News &amp; Updates</a></li>                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                
                <div class="t4a_post_content">
                	<div class="t4a_post_comments t4a_link_noborder">
                    	                    	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/news/applepi-baker-v1-4-update/#comments" title="<i class='icon-comments-alt'></i> Comments - Give us your opinion, and read opinions of others ... - No comments have been placed so far."><i class="icon-comments-alt"></i> 0</a>
                    </div>
                	<p>ApplePi-Baker, the application I developed for Mac OS X user that like to work with the Raspberry Pi, is now available in version 1.4.<br />
With ApplePi-Baker, you can write an IMG file to an SD-Card, prepare an SD-Card for NOOBS use, and make a backup of an SD-Card.</p>
<p>The changes involves fixing a minore bug (proper sizing of an SD-Card vs IMG file) and a minor speed improvement. If you haven&#8217;t run into any issue, then this update might not be needed for your purposes.</p>
<p>See the <a title="MacOS X – ApplePi Baker – Prep SD-Cards for IMG or NOOBS" href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/hardware/raspberry-pi/macosx-apple-pi-baker/">ApplePi-Baker article</a> or the <a title="Downloadable Files" href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/downloads/">Downloads Page</a> for download and details.</p>
                </div>
            
                        
            </div>
            
                        
