                    <h2><a href='http://www.tweaking4all.com/qnap/pyload-put-io/'>QNAP &#8211; Tweaking and using pyLoad for Put.io downloads &#8230;</a></h2>
                </div> 
                
                <div class="t4a_post_image t4a_link_noborder">
                	<img src="http://www.tweaking4all.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/feature-image-putio-pyload-qnap.png" alt="QNAP &#8211; Tweaking and using pyLoad for Put.io downloads &#8230;" width="180" height="151"/><ul><li style="color:#444"><i class="icon-user"></i><ul><li title="Level of Difficulty - <strong>Moderate</strong> - The average user should be able to do this, but read the details!"><i class="icon-star"></i><i class="icon-star"></i><i class="icon-star-empty"></i></li></ul></li></ul>                    
                    
                    
					                    <ul><li><i class="icon-folder-close-alt">
                    	</i> 
                            <ul>
                            	<li><a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/category/network-internet/" title="<i class='icon-folder-close-alt'> Network - Internet - View all articles in this Category">Network - Internet</a></li><li><a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/category/qnap/" title="<i class='icon-folder-close-alt'> QNAP - View all articles in this Category">QNAP</a></li>                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                
                <div class="t4a_post_content">
                	<div class="t4a_post_comments t4a_link_noborder">
                    	                    	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/qnap/pyload-put-io/#comments" title="<i class='icon-comments-alt'></i> Comments - Give us your opinion, and read opinions of others ... - No comments have been placed so far."><i class="icon-comments-alt"></i> 0</a>
                    </div>
                	<p>If you&#8217;re familiar with the <strong><a title="Put.io - Cloud Service that can download torrents for you ..." href="http://put.io" target="_blank">Put.io</a></strong> service (<a title="Put.io – Download torrent safely with a cloud service …" href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/network-internet/put-io-download-torrent-safely/">article</a>) then using <a title="pyLoad - Free Download Manager written in Python" href="http://pyload.org/" target="_blank"><strong>pyLoad</strong></a> as your download manager is your best choice (at this moment) when running it on a <a title="QNAP - My favorite NAS!" href="http://www.qnap.com/" target="_blank">QNAP</a>.</p>
<p>Put.io is a service that downloads <a title="Wiki - Torrent" href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Torrent" target="_blank">torrents</a> for you to their cloud service, where you have your own private space so you can download it from there like any other file. Put.io even supports the use download managers that split downloads into multiple chunks so that you can maximize your Internet bandwidth (they even recommend it).</p>
<p>Other download managers on the QNAP however do not support multiple chunks, so you&#8217;re &#8220;stuck&#8221; with pyLoad and that&#8217;s where you might run into small issues, but we will get to that into this article.</p>
                </div>
            
                        	<div class="t4a_continue_reading t4a_link_noborder">
                	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/qnap/pyload-put-io/" title="<i class='icon-file-alt'></i> Read More - Continue reading the rest of the article">
                    	<i class="icon-caret-right"></i><i class="icon-caret-right"></i>&nbsp;Continue reading …  
                    </a>
                </div>
                        
            </div>
            
                        
        <!-- END: Post -->
            
        	        
            <!-- START: Post -->
            <div class="t4a_post" id="post-3485">
            
            	<div class="t4a_post_title_box">
                	<div class="t4a_post_date">
                        <div class="t4a_post_day_year">
                        	<div class="t4a_post_date_month">APR</div>
                            <div class="t4a_post_date_year">2014</div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="t4a_post_date_day">06</div>
                    </div>
                    <h2><a href='http://www.tweaking4all.com/network-internet/put-io-download-torrent-safely/'>Put.io &#8211; Download torrent safely with a cloud service &#8230;</a></h2>
                </div> 
                
                <div class="t4a_post_image t4a_link_noborder">
                	<img src="http://www.tweaking4all.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/featured_image_putio.png" alt="Put.io &#8211; Download torrent safely with a cloud service &#8230;" width="180" height="151"/><ul><li style="color:#444"><i class="icon-user"></i><ul><li title="Level of Difficulty - <strong>Easy</strong> - With careful reading, anyone should be able to do this."><i class="icon-star"></i><i class="icon-star-empty"></i><i class="icon-star-empty"></i></li></ul></li></ul>                    
                    
                    
					                    <ul><li><i class="icon-folder-close-alt">
                    	</i> 
                            <ul>
                            	<li><a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/category/network-internet/" title="<i class='icon-folder-close-alt'> Network - Internet - View all articles in this Category">Network - Internet</a></li>                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                                    </div>
                
                <div class="t4a_post_content">
                	<div class="t4a_post_comments t4a_link_noborder">
                    	                    	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/network-internet/put-io-download-torrent-safely/#comments" title="<i class='icon-comments-alt'></i> Comments - Give us your opinion, and read opinions of others ... - No comments have been placed so far."><i class="icon-comments-alt"></i> 0</a>
                    </div>
                	<p>Downloading a torrent safely can be tricky. All kinds of options and services out there offer you privacy protection and most of them (VPN&#8217;s for example) can be cumbersome to setup or maintain, and are often slower than the real deal.</p>
<p><strong><a title="Put.io - Cloud Service that can download torrents for you ..." href="http://put.io" target="_blank">Put.io</a></strong> however offers a cloud service that does all this for you. It downloads (and even seeds) a torrent safely for you into their cloud service and stores the downloaded files in your private storage space (starts at 50Gb!!)<span style="line-height: 1.5em;">.</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">Once a download has been completed, you can then download the downloaded torrent as a regular file. They recommend and support the use of a Download Manager to get the maximum speed out of your Internet connection.</span></p>
<p><span style="line-height: 1.5em;">For $0.99 you can take it for a spin for a day and you&#8217;ll be surprised how well it works.</span></p>
                </div>
            
                        	<div class="t4a_continue_reading t4a_link_noborder">
                	<a href="http://www.tweaking4all.com/network-internet/put-io-download-torrent-safely/" title="<i class='icon-file-alt'></i> Read More - Continue reading the rest of the article">
                    	<i class="icon-caret-right"></i><i class="icon-caret-right"></i>&nbsp;Continue reading …  
                    </a>
                </div>
                        
            </div>
            
                        
